@node "WhatIS" "What Is DizIT?"
@next "Legal"
@prev "Main"
What is DizIT?

Ah, usual story! I needed something, but was not able to find it, so I made
it!

Hm! In fact, i found 'it', but 'it' used to reset my machine, or to block
it. So, I needed just ordinary 'dizzer' (!?) that will extract all
FILE_ID.DIZ's from all files in single directory. I didn't have a clue on
programming, but... I simply NEEDED it! :) So, I was forced to learn a bit
of C, and to create this. DizIT is my first program in C (excluding "Hello
World" thing! :).

DizIT is a simple 'dizzer', that will extract all FILE_ID.DIZ's from all
files in single directory (like i've heard it before...), and place them in
text file, which look like (kind of :) AmiExpress filelisting.

It is written in C, but no source is available, because it would probably
make You laugh loudly! :)

