@node "Require" "Requirements"
@next "Install"
@prev "Legal"


- An Amiga
- Kickstart 3.X
- Directory full of archives
- Unfortunatelly, You will need following executables:

* Lha
* Lzx
* DMSDescript
* TxtExtract
* ExeDescript
* Unzip

They will be used for extracting FILE_ID.DIZ's from archives/files. I
supplied DMSDescript, TxtExtract and ExeDecript in this archive. I certainly
hope authors of these programs won't be angry, but I am not quite sure if
these executables are 'gettable' from AmiNet.

LhA, Lzx and Unzip can be found on AmiNet.

DizIT was tested on A4000/040 with OS3.0. I suppose it will work on 3.1 too,
but haven't tested it on OS2.X (yet...).

@{"NeXT" link "Install" 0}
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Require"


Installation is quite hard & complicated.

You have to copy DizIT to i.e. C: directory on You hard disk. You have to
copy DizIT.guide wherever You want.

@{"NeXT" link "Usage" 0}
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Author"
@prev "Install"


DizIT has 2 arguments, and they are:

<directory>   = directory which contains archives you want to be 'dizzed'
<result file> = text file which will be created

Example:

3.Ram Disk:> DizIT Dh2:DownLoad FILE_ID.LIST



DizIT will NOT print the FILE_ID.DIZ on screen, but will show the filename
of file 'in progress'.  In case of some error, the filename will stay on
screen, so You can check later what was wrong.

Take care, DizIT will extract FILE_ID.DIZ's to RAM:, so make sure You have
one around!  :)

Also, I hope there will be no problems with 'protected' FILE_ID.DIZ's, which
have -d attribute set (i.e. ----rwe-).

I must admit that DizIT is much faster than I ever expected (hm! :), and
that is the main reason why I 'released' it.

